      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Validation — Nominal Operating Point",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) compared against in-vitro experimental measurements at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM). The predicted RH value of 0.81 fell within the experimental uncertainty band (0.74–0.89), satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The activity that generated this result is not recorded in the structured record; only the numerical outcome is reported here.",
